First, we need to find the symmetric difference (Δ) between sets A and B. The symmetric difference is the set of elements which are in either of the sets A or B, but not in their intersection.

A Δ B = (A ∪ B) - (A ∩ B)

The union of A and B (A ∪ B) is the set of all elements in either A or B:

A ∪ B = {1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 8}

The intersection of A and B (A ∩ B) is the set of all elements that are common to both A and B:

A ∩ B = {2, 4}

Now, we can find the symmetric difference (A Δ B):

A Δ B = {1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 8} - {2, 4} = {1, 3, 6, 8}

Next, we need to find the union of the symmetric difference (A Δ B) and the set {5}:

(A Δ B) ∪ {5} = {1, 3, 6, 8} ∪ {5} = {1, 3, 5, 6, 8}

So, (A Δ B) ∪ {5} = {1, 3, 5, 6, 8}.
